  "text": "In contrast to active ␤-catenin, pre-TCR signaling considerably induced TCF-1 levels. Together with the activation of the wnt reporter at the pre-TCR stage, these findings imply that induction of TCF-1 is the critical pre-TCR-dependent event, which integrates pre-TCR with wnt signals. The importance of regulating TCF-1 levels is also supported by the analysis of p45 TCF-1 Tg mice. The abundance of the Tg p45 protein corresponds approximately to that of the endogenous p45 in total thymocytes. [CITATION_1] However, the amount of the Tg p45 TCF-1 is fixed and not subject to the normal regulation of the endogenous TCF-1 locus. Indeed, the p45 Tg only partially rescued T-cell development at the pre-TCR stage.",
